<subSubSection lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="138" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1628,2013]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,1628,1653]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus box="[324,372,1629,1653]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">type</typeStatus>
species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Bonnier, 1900" authorityName="Bonnier" authorityYear="1900" box="[498,817,1628,1653]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[498,649,1629,1652]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">Trapezicepon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Bonnier, J." box="[656,817,1628,1653]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 476" refId="ref8566" refString="Bonnier, J. (1900) Contribution a l'etude des epicarides. Les Bopyridae. Travaux de la Station Zoologique de Wimereux, 8, 1 - 476, pls. 1 - 41." type="journal article" year="1900">Bonnier, 1900</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Giard &amp; Bonnier, 1888)" authorityName="Giard &amp; Bonnier" authorityYear="1888" baseAuthorityName="Giard &amp; Bonnier" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[829,1257,1628,1653]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amicorum">
<emphasis box="[829,842,1629,1652]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[857,971,1629,1652]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">amicorum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Giard, A. &amp; Bonnier, J." box="[985,1249,1628,1653]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" pagination="44 - 47" refId="ref9194" refString="Giard, A. &amp; Bonnier, J. (1888) Sur quelques especes nouvelles de ceponiens. Comptes Rendus Hebdomadaires des Seances de l'Academie de Sciences, 107, 44 - 47." type="journal article" year="1888">Giard &amp; Bonnier, 1888</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, is quite similar in many characters to species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Giard &amp; Bonnier" authorityYear="1887" box="[517,662,1664,1687]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Cancricepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[517,662,1664,1687]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">Cancricepon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, especially to 
<taxonomicName authority="An &amp; Wang &amp; Boyko &amp; Williams, 2019" authorityName="An &amp; Wang &amp; Boyko &amp; Williams" authorityYear="2019" box="[824,934,1664,1688]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Cancricepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="castroi" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[824,843,1664,1687]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[857,934,1665,1688]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">castroi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[941,1004,1663,1688]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[941,1004,1663,1688]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
The most obvious difference is that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Giard &amp; Bonnier" baseAuthorityYear="1888" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amicorum">
<emphasis box="[1415,1428,1665,1688]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,265,1701,1724]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">amicorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has been reported infesting 
<taxonomicName authority="(Herbst, 1801)" authorityName="Herbst" authorityYear="1801" baseAuthorityName="Herbst" baseAuthorityYear="1801" box="[661,1047,1700,1725]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Trapezia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cymodoce">
<emphasis box="[661,878,1700,1725]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">Trapezia cymodoce</emphasis>
(Herbst, 1801)
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[1062,1197,1700,1725]" class="Malacostraca" family="Trapeziidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Trapeziidae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Bonnier, J." box="[1219,1380,1700,1725]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" pagination="1 - 476" refId="ref8566" refString="Bonnier, J. (1900) Contribution a l'etude des epicarides. Les Bopyridae. Travaux de la Station Zoologique de Wimereux, 8, 1 - 476, pls. 1 - 41." type="journal article" year="1900">Bonnier, 1900</bibRefCitation>
) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Dana, 1852" authorityName="Dana" authorityYear="1852" box="[151,535,1735,1760]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Actumnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tomentosus">
<emphasis box="[151,396,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">Actumnus tomentosus</emphasis>
Dana, 1852
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authority="(De Haan, 1835)" authorityName="De Haan" authorityYear="1835" baseAuthorityName="De Haan" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[578,882,1735,1760]" class="Malacostraca" family="Xanthidae" genus="Actumnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="setifer">
<emphasis box="[578,595,1736,1759]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[611,681,1736,1760]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">setifer</emphasis>
(De Haan, 1835)
</taxonomicName>
] (
<taxonomicName authorityName="Samouelle" authorityYear="1819" box="[905,1036,1735,1760]" class="Malacostraca" family="Pilumnidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Pilumnidae</taxonomicName>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Stebbing, T. R. R." box="[1061,1237,1735,1760]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" pagination="83 - 122" refId="ref10389" refString="Stebbing, T. R. R. (1910) No. VI. - Isopoda from the Indian Ocean and British East Africa. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London, 2 nd ser., Zoology, 14, 83 - 122, pls. 5 - 11." type="journal article" year="1910">Stebbing, 1910</bibRefCitation>
), lacks middorsal projections on any pereomeres of the female. The barbula is similar in both species in that there are two falcate lateral projections on each side but differs in that 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Giard &amp; Bonnier" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[700,840,1808,1832]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amicorum">
<emphasis box="[700,713,1809,1832]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[727,840,1809,1832]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">amicorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a broad, flat median region, whereas members of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Giard &amp; Bonnier" authorityYear="1887" box="[265,410,1845,1868]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Cancricepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[265,410,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">Cancricepon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have a median region with a pair of blunt triangular projections. The males of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Giard &amp; Bonnier" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1295,1436,1845,1868]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amicorum">
<emphasis box="[1295,1308,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1322,1436,1845,1868]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">amicorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Giard &amp; Bonnier" authorityYear="1887" box="[205,350,1880,1903]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Cancricepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[205,350,1880,1903]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">Cancricepon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. are nearly indistinguishable. It appears that these two genera are closely related and molecular data would be helpful in determining if their status as separate genera is warranted.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1628,2013]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,717]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="138" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">
A second species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonnier" authorityYear="1900" box="[436,587,1953,1976]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[436,587,1953,1976]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">Trapezicepon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Danforth, 1972" authorityName="Danforth" authorityYear="1972" box="[603,925,1951,1976]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="domeciae">
<emphasis box="[603,616,1953,1976]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[632,739,1951,1976]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">domeciae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Danforth, C. G." box="[749,925,1951,1976]" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" pagination="163 - 177" refId="ref9059" refString="Danforth, C. G. (1972) New bopyrids (Isopoda) from the Indian and Pacific Oceans. Micronesica, 7, 163 - 177." type="journal article" year="1972">Danforth, 1972</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, was incompletely described and figured but appears to be congeneric with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Giard &amp; Bonnier" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[503,646,1989,2012]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amicorum">
<emphasis box="[503,516,1989,2012]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[533,646,1989,2012]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">amicorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and therefore also closely related to 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Giard &amp; Bonnier" authorityYear="1887" box="[1075,1220,1989,2012]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Cancricepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="1" pageNumber="137" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1075,1220,1989,2012]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="137">Cancricepon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. However, the third described species in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonnier" authorityYear="1900" box="[442,593,153,176]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[442,593,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Trapezicepon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Markham, 1985" authorityName="Markham" authorityYear="1985" box="[607,944,151,176]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thalamitae">
<emphasis box="[607,620,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[635,755,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">thalamitae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Markham, J. C." box="[762,944,151,176]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" pagination="1 - 63" refId="ref9482" refString="Markham, J. C. (1985) Additions to the bopyrid isopod fauna of Thailand. Zoologische Ferhandelingen, 224, 1 - 63." type="journal article" year="1985">Markham, 1985</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, is clearly not congeneric with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Giard &amp; Bonnier" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[1295,1436,152,176]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amicorum">
<emphasis box="[1295,1308,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1322,1436,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">amicorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nor closely related to any species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonnier" authorityYear="1900" box="[607,758,189,212]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[607,758,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Trapezicepon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName=", Giard &amp; Bonnier" authorityYear="1887" box="[809,954,189,212]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Cancricepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[809,954,189,212]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Cancricepon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This conclusion is based on numerous characters of the female and male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Markham" authorityYear="1985" box="[619,774,223,248]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thalamitae">
<emphasis box="[619,632,225,248]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[654,774,223,248]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">thalamitae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
including: female with large middorsal projections on pereomeres 6 and 
<quantity box="[357,401,260,285]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.778" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" unit="in" value="7.0">7 in</quantity>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Markham" authorityYear="1985" box="[408,556,260,285]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thalamitae">
<emphasis box="[408,421,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[436,556,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">thalamitae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. none in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Giard &amp; Bonnier" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[694,837,261,284]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amicorum">
<emphasis box="[694,707,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[723,837,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">amicorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male with head much narrower than first pereomere in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Markham" authorityYear="1985" box="[183,334,295,320]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thalamitae">
<emphasis box="[183,196,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[214,334,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">thalamitae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. subequal in width in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Giard &amp; Bonnier" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[637,781,296,320]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amicorum">
<emphasis box="[637,650,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[668,781,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">amicorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and male with medial dorsal fusion of pleomeres in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Markham" authorityYear="1985" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thalamitae">
<emphasis box="[1415,1428,297,320]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,271,332,357]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">thalamitae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
vs. pleomeres completely separated in 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Giard &amp; Bonnier" baseAuthorityYear="1888" box="[751,899,333,356]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amicorum">
<emphasis box="[751,764,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[785,899,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">amicorum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In fact, these three characters show that 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Markham" authorityYear="1985" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thalamitae">
<emphasis box="[1415,1428,333,356]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,271,367,392]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">thalamitae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to 
<taxonomicName authority="Tattersall, 1905" authorityName="Tattersall" authorityYear="1905" box="[406,725,367,392]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Scyracepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[406,537,368,391]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Scyracepon</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Tattersall, W. M." box="[546,725,367,392]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" pagination="1 - 90" refId="ref10442" refString="Tattersall, W. M. (1905) Appendix, No. II. The marine fauna of the coast of Ireland. Part V. Isopoda. Fisheries, Ireland, Scientific Investigations, 1904, 2, 1 - 90, pls. 1 - 11, 2 unnumbered charts." type="journal article" year="1905">Tattersall, 1905</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, a genus in which females of all species have large middorsal projections on at least pereomeres 6 and 7, males have a head much narrower than the first pereomere, and males have medial dorsal fusion of all pleomeres. We therefore formally transfer 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Markham" authorityYear="1985" box="[1036,1187,439,464]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thalamitae">
<emphasis box="[1036,1049,441,464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">T</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1067,1187,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">thalamitae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tattersall" authorityYear="1905" box="[1231,1362,440,463]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Scyracepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1231,1362,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Scyracepon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as 
<taxonomicName authority="(Markham, 1985)" authorityName="An &amp; Wang &amp; Boyko &amp; Williams" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Markham" baseAuthorityYear="1985" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thalamitae" status="n. comb.">
<emphasis box="[1415,1429,440,463]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[151,271,476,501]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">thalamitae</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Markham, J. C." box="[285,467,476,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" pagination="1 - 63" refId="ref9482" refString="Markham, J. C. (1985) Additions to the bopyrid isopod fauna of Thailand. Zoologische Ferhandelingen, 224, 1 - 63." type="journal article" year="1985">Markham, 1985</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[482,584,476,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[482,584,476,501]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" rank="species">n. comb.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,151,717]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">
An additional juvenile female found parasitizing an unidentified species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Leach 1815" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1815" box="[1138,1394,511,536]" class="Malacostraca" family="Parthenopidae" genus="Lambrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1138,1238,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Lambrus</emphasis>
Leach 1815
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<emphasis box="[151,282,548,573]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Parthenope</emphasis>
Weber, 1795) was identified as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bonnier" authorityYear="1900" box="[644,795,549,572]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Trapezicepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[644,795,549,572]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Trapezicepon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. by Nierstrasz &amp; Brender à 
<bibRefCitation author="Nierstrasz, H. F. &amp; Brandis, G. A." box="[1144,1317,548,573]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" pagination="147 - 226" refId="ref9848" refString="Nierstrasz, H. F. &amp; Brender a Brandis, G. A. (1931) Papers from Dr. Th. Mortensen's Pacific Expedition 1914 - 16. LVII. Epicaridea II. Fidenskabelige Meddedelser fra den Dansk Naturhistoriske Forening i KObenhavn, 91, 147 - 226, pl. 1." type="journal article" year="1931">Brandis (1931)</bibRefCitation>
. However, due to the specimen’s immaturity, its generic placement is unclear and it could belong to any one of a number of keponine genera, including 
<taxonomicName authority="Nierstrasz &amp; Brender" authorityName="Nierstrasz &amp; Brender" authorityYear="1930" box="[477,851,620,645]" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Apocepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[477,589,620,643]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">Apocepon</emphasis>
Nierstrasz &amp; Brender
</taxonomicName>
à 
<bibRefCitation author="Nierstrasz, H. F. &amp; Brandis, G. A." box="[887,1052,620,645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" pagination="147 - 226" refId="ref9848" refString="Nierstrasz, H. F. &amp; Brender a Brandis, G. A. (1931) Papers from Dr. Th. Mortensen's Pacific Expedition 1914 - 16. LVII. Epicaridea II. Fidenskabelige Meddedelser fra den Dansk Naturhistoriske Forening i KObenhavn, 91, 147 - 226, pl. 1." type="journal article" year="1931">Brandis, 1931</bibRefCitation>
, whose 
<typeStatus box="[1152,1200,621,645]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">type</typeStatus>
species, 
<taxonomicName authority="Nierstrasz &amp; Brender" authorityName="Nierstrasz &amp; Brender" class="Malacostraca" family="Bopyridae" genus="Apocepon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Isopoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibogae">
<emphasis box="[1313,1330,620,643]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1349,1436,620,645]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="138">sibogae</emphasis>
Nierstrasz &amp; Brender
</taxonomicName>
à 
<bibRefCitation author="Nierstrasz, H. F. &amp; Brandis, G. A." box="[442,607,655,680]" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" pagination="147 - 226" refId="ref9848" refString="Nierstrasz, H. F. &amp; Brender a Brandis, G. A. (1931) Papers from Dr. Th. Mortensen's Pacific Expedition 1914 - 16. LVII. Epicaridea II. Fidenskabelige Meddedelser fra den Dansk Naturhistoriske Forening i KObenhavn, 91, 147 - 226, pl. 1." type="journal article" year="1931">Brandis, 1931</bibRefCitation>
, contains the only other bopyrid specimen (also a female) known to parasitize a host in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="MacLeay" authorityYear="1838" box="[367,531,692,717]" class="Malacostraca" family="Parthenopidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="family">Parthenopidae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
